{"id":"1412.7981","submitter":"Eduardo Sergio Santini","authors":"E. Sergio Santini (CNEN & CBPF-Brasil)","title":"Is there a super-selection rule in quantum cosmology?","comments":"11 pages 13 figures","journal-ref":"Gravit. Cosmol. (2019) 25: 226","doi":"10.1134/S0202289319030101","report-no":null,"categories":"gr-qc","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A certain approach to solving the Wheeler-DeWitt equation in quantum\ncosmology, which is based on a type of super-selection rule by which negative\nfrequency solutions are discarded, is discussed. In a preliminary analysis, we\nrecall well known results in relativistic quantum field theory, showing that\nadopt this approach of super-selection by discarding a sector of the\nfrequencies, does not lead to acceptable results. In the area of quantum\ncosmology a qualitatively similar result is obtained: we show that by\ndiscarding solutions of negative frequencies, which is usually done in order to\ndemonstrate \"strong\" results on the resolution of the singularity, important\nphysical processes are lost, namely the existence of cyclic solutions which,\nunder certain reasonable assumptions, can be interpreted as processes of\ncreation-annihilation at the Planck scale, which are typical of any\nrelativistic quantum field theory.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 26 Dec 2014 19:56:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Jan 2016 14:10:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 27 Jan 2016 19:32:53 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 25 Oct 2019 21:40:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-06"}
